Managing a business as a creative introvert who is very private should not be complicated, yet it often is. Most online resources and coaches tell you to work with the big (and evil) technology companies using extroverted techniques. Promote here, follow the algorithm, share who you are. Get your service reviewed, be available 24/7, answer questions with a video of yourself, respond immediately. Video, video, video.
01/03/2024
This is a year of transition for me.
I do not want to feed my money, data, and energy to large technology companies. Nor do I want coaches who have only one extroverted solution they apply to everyone. I am exploring new ways to manage my activity while fighting against the idea I long believed, that things must be done a certain way to succeed.
Wish me luck!
I have already taken the first steps.
I left Facebook, removed all Meta and Pinterest trackers from my website, and deleted my private WhatsApp account.
I also removed the last external tracker, Google Analytics, from my website yesterday, and it feels great.
I recently subscribed to a European-based CRM for better GDPR compliance, and I will transfer my activity over the next few weeks.
I transferred my MX to Proton and now fully enjoy SPF, DKIM, and DMAR without having to pay Google for basic email address validation.
03/03/2024
